The paper presents algorithms for generating anticliques and calculating the independence polynomial of a graph, which are topics related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorial geometry (cs.CG). The use of branch and bound techniques also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the use of Mathematica for programming suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
